<paragraph id="2E605604FFD2FF850790FDC712C68E22" blockId="15.[143,1104,561,783]" box="[143,251,561,584]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">
<heading id="7528E168FFD2FF850790FDC712C68E22" box="[143,251,561,584]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552" reason="5">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFD2FF850790FDC712C68E22" box="[143,251,561,584]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFD2FF850790FDA110828F65" blockId="15.[143,1104,561,783]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFD2FF85061EFDAE135E8E1A" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2001" box="[257,355,600,624]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mihun">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFD2FF85061EFDAE135E8E1A" box="[257,355,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">J. mihun</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFD2FF8505A5FDAE111F8E1A" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Jager" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[698,802,600,624]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thakek" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFD2FF8505A5FDAE111F8E1A" box="[698,802,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">J. thakek</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFD2FF850432FDA111918E05" box="[813,940,599,623]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the strongly excavated apico-prolateral side of the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFD2FF85040FFD8111AC8EE5" box="[784,913,631,655]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[211,278,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Jacaena spp. Male palps, ventral (A, D, G). Ditto, prolateral (B, E, H). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F, I). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (originally misidentified as Sesieutes schwendingeri) (D–F); J. mihun, holotype (G–I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517648/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">Figures 4G</figureCitation>
cf. 5G), and the short conductor (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFD2FF850647FD6113E78EC5" box="[344,474,663,687]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[211,278,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-5@8.[213,1170,168,1394]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Jacaena spp. Male palps, ventral (A, D, G). Ditto, prolateral (B, E, H). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F, I). Jacaena schwendingeri comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (originally misidentified as Sesieutes schwendingeri) (D–F); J. mihun, holotype (G–I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517648/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">Figures 4H</figureCitation>
cf. 5H), but can be distinguished by the presence of a small triangular denticle on the dorsal surface of the conductor (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFD2FF850443FD4111DC8EA5" box="[860,993,695,719]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="18.[211,278,1446,1468]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,167,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-5@18.[213,1170,167,1413]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 10. Jacaena mihun, holotype (A–C); J. thakek comb. nov., holotype (D–F). Male palp, ventral (A, D). Ditto, prolateral (B, E). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517670/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). Females can be recognised by the tremendously lengthened insemination ducts strongly convoluted; spermathecae are indistinct (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFD2FF850508FD01108E8F65" box="[535,691,759,783]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="14.[211,278,950,972]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,169,916]" captionTargetId="figure-5@14.[213,1170,169,917]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 8. Jacaena spp. Internal copulatory organ, dorsal (A–G). Jacaena mihun (A–D); J. angoonae sp. nov., holotype (E); J. schwendingeri comb. nov., paratype (F); J. lunulata sp. nov., paratype (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517664/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1552">Figure 8A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
